`` In no way the problem can be solved without India playing a positive role , '' Solheim told the press here following his talks with Indian External Affairs Minister Jaswant Singh on the situation in the island country .
Solheim , who has been trying to facilitate a dialogue between the Sri Lankan government and the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam -LRB- LTTE -RRB- , was here on a day 's visit to discuss with India the situation in Sri Lanka .
He also held a meeting with Indian Foreign Secretary Lalit Mansingh .
An Indian External Affairs Ministry spokesman said Solheim shared India 's approach that the solution to the ethnic conflict lay with the Sri Lankans themselves in a manner by which all communities could realize their aspirations within the context of the unity , sovereignty and territorial integrity of the country .
Also on Thursday , Indian Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee ruled out any possibility of a change in India 's policy in the event of fall of Jaffna to the LTTE , which has launched an all-out offensive against government troops to wrest control of the northern Sri Lankan peninsula .
